Class AbstractBaseLogic

  • java.lang.Object
    • simpplle.comcode.logic.AbstractBaseLogic
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BaseLogic, VegUnitFireTypeLogic

    public abstract class AbstractBaseLogic
extends java.lang.Object
    The University of Montana owns copyright of the designated documentation contained within this file as part of the software product designated by Uniform Resource Identifier UM-OpenSIMPPLLE-1.0.     This class defines the base logic for the System. It is an abstract class and therefore cannot be instantiated. It is subclassed by many other classes. For an understanding of the base logic for the system see BaseLogic.java.

      • AbstractBaseLogic

        protected AbstractBaseLogic(java.lang.String[] kinds)
        This method forms the abstract base for kinds of system processes which are used in the table columns. While this class is abstract it is good to note here the base columns for OpenSimpplle are set in BaseLogic.java and are ECO_GROUP_COL, "SPECIES_COL",SIZE_CLASS_COL","DENSITY_COL", "PROCESS_COL", "TREATMENT_COL", "SEASON_COL", "MOISTURE_COL","TEMP_COL","TRACKING_SPECIES_COL","OWNERSHIP_COL","SPECIAL_AREA_COL","ROAD_STATUS_COL","TRAIL_STATUS_COL","LANDTYPE_COL"
        Parameters:
        kinds - logic kinds which are to be made into visible columns

      • addColumn

        protected void addColumn(java.lang.String kind,
             java.lang.String column)
        Adds a column to the string ArrayList of columns for a particular kind of Base Logic. This all happens within the columns hashmap >
        Parameters:
        kind - the logic kind. This is the key for the columns
        column - This is the string representation of column. for example ROW_COL which has an final int value of 0 or SPECIES_COL which has a final int value of LAST_COL + 2 within the Base Logic class.

      • moveRowUp

        public int moveRowUp(int row,
            java.lang.String kind)
        This moves a row up in the GUI table models by creating a new temporary row to hold the row information, then removing the row and setting the temporary row to row number minus 1. There is a check to make sure the row is not <0. It then adds the row to the data kind arraylist.
        Parameters:
        row - row to be moved upward
        kind - the logic data kind.
        Returns:
        the int representing the new row

      • moveRowDown

        public int moveRowDown(int row,
              java.lang.String kind)
        This moves a row down in the GUI table models by creating a new temporary row to hold the row information, then removing the row and setting the temporary row to row number plus 1. There is a check to make sure the row is not greater than the data arraylist for the particlar logic data kind. It then adds the row to the data kind arraylist.
        Parameters:
        row - row to be moved upward
        kind - the logic data kind.
        Returns:
        the int representing the new row
